definitions: the most perfect or typical example of a quality or class
examples: This painting is the quintessence of Renaissance art

definitions: a musical composition for five performers or a group of five people
examples: The string quintet performed Mozart beautifully last night

definitions: a number or amount that is five times as great as another
examples: The company achieved a quintuple increase in profits
She won the quintuple of her original bet

definitions: a clever or funny remark made during conversation
examples: His quip about the weather lightened the mood
She always had a quip ready for any situation

definitions: an unusual habit or way of behaving that someone has
examples: One of his quirks is arranging books by color

definitions: a case for holding arrows used in archery
a slight trembling movement or sound
examples: The archer reached for an arrow from her quiver

definitions: a test of knowledge especially as a competition or brief informal examination
examples: The teacher gave a surprise quiz on Friday
They participated in the weekly pub quiz downtown

definitions: the minimum number of members required to be present for valid meeting proceedings
examples: We cannot vote without a quorum of members present

definitions: a limited quantity of something that is officially allowed or required

definitions: a Jewish scholar or teacher especially of Jewish law and tradition

definitions: a disorderly crowd of people viewed as worthless or unruly

definitions: a deadly viral disease that affects the nervous system of mammals
examples: The dog was quarantined after showing signs of rabies
Vaccination programs have greatly reduced rabies cases worldwide

definitions: a greyish-brown American mammal with a black mask around its eyes and ringed tail
examples: A raccoon was rummaging through our garbage last night
The raccoon washed its food in the stream

definitions: a track or grounds where horse or vehicle races are held

definitions: a horse bred and trained specifically for racing competitions
examples: The racehorse won by three lengths at the track

definitions: a person or animal that competes in races professionally or recreationally

Several amateur racers joined the weekend cycling competition

definitions: an oval or circular course built for racing competitions

definitions: a track or channel for racing or water flow

Cable management improved after adding the new raceway system

definitions: the sport or business of competing in races with vehicles or animals

She developed a passion for motorcycle racing

definitions: a bat with strings stretched across it used in tennis and similar games

definitions: a person who engages in dishonest and fraudulent business dealings

definitions: dishonest and fraudulent business dealings especially as part of organized crime
examples: He was convicted of racketeering and money laundering charges

definitions: alternative spelling of racket used in sports like tennis or squash

definitions: a game played with a small rubber ball and short racquets in an enclosed court
examples: They play racquetball every Tuesday at the gym

definitions: arranged like rays or spokes spreading outward from a central point

definitions: light or heat as emitted or reflected by something

definitions: a device for heating rooms consisting of metal pipes through which hot water flows

A damaged radiator caused the engine to overheat

definitions: a lottery with goods as prizes typically held to raise funds
